# Part E: pg_hba.conf entry required to let the "replicator" role open a
# streaming-replication connection from the standby (or, in this lab, from
# the local machine acting as the standby's host).
#
# Placed ABOVE any broader "host replication all ... trust/md5" line so it
# is actually the entry that gets matched for this specific role.

# TYPE  DATABASE        USER            ADDRESS                 METHOD
host    replication     replicator      127.0.0.1/32            md5
